No Degree View Instruction 13

1.Right Click the NO IT Exp worksheet and Duplicate it.

2. Rename worksheet to No Degree

3. Remove [IT Exp] from the Rows shelf

4. Move _cc.CountEntireTable from the Column shelf to the Rows shelf.

5. In the Marks card, replace _cc.IT Exp% with _with cc.NoDegree% for Detail. Also remove Agg(_cc.Gendermale>Female)


Final View


 6. In the Marks Card, drag Education Group onto Text(Label).



 7. Drag _cc.CountEntireTable onto Size

 8. Drag _cc.CountEntireTable onto Text(Label).


 9. Click on analysis in the menu. Select Percentage of then select table.


 10. In the Marks Card, right click the _cc.CountEntireTable that is in Text(Label)


 11. Select Format. Go to Numbers, under Default. Select Percentage, 1 Decimal place.


 12. Click on the Descending Order icon in the menu up top(Underneath the word “Window”)
 13. Change the View from Standard to Entire View



 14. Hide the Size legend



 15. Double Click Title.
 16. Highlight Missing Field. Click on Insert and Select cc.NoDegree% and make it Tableau Bold , Font 24, Bold and Grey                 black(#333333) click space type No Degree. Highlight No Degree and make it Tableau Book, Font 18, Bold and Pink(#fe019a).


 17. Replace No IT Exp with No Degree.


 18. Right Click the Y Axis and uncheck Show Header



 19. If Tooltip is not working. In the Marks Card, click on Tooltip

 20. Highlight the MissingField for Male. Click on Insert and select _cc_Gender=Male)

 21. Highlight the Missinng Filed for Female. Click on the insert the select_cc_Gender=Female

 22. Tooltip should look like 

           Male: <% of Total SUM(_cc_Gender=Male)>
          Female: <% of Total SUM(_cc_Gender=Female)>
